posts.title: It ends with Us
posts.content: The story follows florist Lily Bloom, whose abusive relationship with neurosurgeon Ryle Kincaid is compounded when her high school boyfriend Atlas Corrigan re-enters her life. It explores themes of domestic violence and emotional abuse
posts.author: Collen Hoover

posts.title: It starts with us
posts.content: The novel continues from where It Ends with Us ended and centers on the relationship between Lily and Atlas.[3] It alternates chapters between the first-person narration of Lily and Atlas.
posts.author: Collen Hoover

posts.title: The seven husbands of Evelyn Hugo
posts.content: Reclusive Hollywood legend Evelyn Hugo chooses an unknown reporter, Monique Grant, to tell her life story. Evelyn recounts her time in the Golden Age of Hollywood, her rise to fame and her seven marriages â€” revealing stunning secrets and lies. But through it all one question remains: Why has she chosen Monique for her final confession?
posts.author: Taylor Jenkins

posts.title: The Great Gatsby
posts.content: A writer and wall street trader, Nick Carraway, finds himself drawn to the past and lifestyle of his mysterious millionaire neighbor, Jay Gatsby, amid the riotous parties of the Jazz Age.
posts.author: F. Scott Fitzgerald
